    "34b9f8080808f468d9f39362ae0f96c4": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "34b9f8080808f468d9f39362ae0f96c4",
      "source_id": "",
      "content": "Substance Network brings self-expression in terms of modern web-publishing to the user, respecting desires for content ownership, privacy and security, and fostering the genuine idea of the internet as a decentralized space for open, collaborative, and democratic expression and discussion. We'd like to witness a society that conquers back the internet as a free medium."
    },
    "153c4a4a1ad199446549488a17c3cb6b": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "153c4a4a1ad199446549488a17c3cb6b",
      "source_id": "",
      "content": "Following Tim Berners-Lee's original idea, the internet should be open to everyone, be decentralized by nature, and provide a means for painless, democratized collaboration and sharing. In an interview recently published onÂ wired.co.ukÂ he emphasizes the threat of for-profit internet monopolies and a 'balkanisation' of the web. He demands a re-decentralisation."
    },
